Title: Assassin for hire (if you have another title I can use tell me, it'd be very much appreciated)<br>
<br>
Story: (Year is 2034, takes place in the planet Mars) This story is about a girl named Saphire who's father was a scientist. Her father and his staff of other scientists were assigned to work on an experiment for the military to use once it was proven to work. Militaries around Mars that colonized there wanted a sort of technology that can somehow make their soldiers stronger, faster, etc.  This certain experiment was known as &quot;HAE&quot; (Human Abilitiy Enhancement) <br>
<br>
After 2 years or so, they had made the machine, they just needed someone to test it out. Saphire volunteered to test it out, for her father, and also because she was in Mar's military so she thought it'd be better to be the first.<br>
<br>
After quite sometime in the machine, Saphire's strength, agility, fighting skills, stealth skills, etc. increased. Whilst in the HAE machine, she was in a deep sleep and was stuck in a tube, frozen, which was inside the machine.<br>
Sometime while Saphire was in the machine, her father was dieing of a deadly virus and so he knew his end would come, he assigned a scientist that was not yet infected with the virus, to help his daughter once she was out.<br>
<br>
A few months later after her father's death, it had been one year and a couple of months in the HAE machine. Finally, she was taken out. She had no memory of what happened in her life before she went into the HAE machine. Therefore, she knew nothing of the world and everything around her. The only thing she knew was how to fight and everything else the machine enhanced her abilities on. The scientist that her father assigned to help her when she was ready to come out, was known as Dr. Adachi. Adachi was infected during the same virus that her father had died of, but he didn't let that get in the way with helping Saphire. He put her in a chair, which was hooked up to a computer covered with wires. With that one computer, in under 2 hours, she knew what she knew before, maybe even a bit more than before. <br>
<br>
After a week Adachi dies at a hospital in a city  in Mars called Zelos. Right before his death, he told Saphire to look for his daughter, Noa Adachi, who will help her when she needs the help. <br>
Saphire looked for Noa, and also a job and a place to live. She found an apartment in Zelos, yet still no job, and no Noa. Saphire couldn't find a regular job, so she took a job that she knew she could do best because of all the skill that is required to do this certain type of job was skill she was exceptional at, and this job was being an assassin (oh yeah and sometimes she does merchant type jobs). She was great with guns, going stealth, exceptional at fighting, she was perfect for the job. She became an assassin for hire. One day Noa finds out where Saphire lives and contacts her and meets with her. Since Noa is a computer hacker, Saphire had only one need for her and that was to hack when she needed it.<br>
<br>
Together, they worked as a team. Somewhere along the story they meet a cop who has jobs for Saphire, and she must do them or she'll end up in jail because she's been doing jobs for the wrong kind of people all a long, but she already knew that they were bad people, as long as she got the money, she whad no problem working with them. Then, Saphire meets a guy whom she may fall in love with. This certain guy (before she even knows him) is a target and some bad guys want killed but instead she tells the bad guys that's he's dead, then hides the guy and gets help from him in some of her jobs/missions, however you wish to call it.<br>
<br>
